subSubSection.paragraph:
Prosternum with very fine short setae. Metepisternum (
Fig. 21
) markedly longer than wide, strongly narrowed posteriorly.

Median lobe of aedeagus (
Figs. 23–25
) in lateral view arcuate on dorsal side, with ventral margin almost straight in middle portion and with apex angularly bent dorsally; ventral side edged laterally in apical part and flattened between margins; terminal lamella (
Fig. 23
) in dorsal view wide, wider than long, concave, strongly narrowed posteriorly, with sides very slightly concave just before narrowly rounded apex. Apical orifice in dorsal position, wide apically. Internal sac without spines, with spiny patch apically.

Female genitalia (
Figs. 26 & 27
): gonocoxite comparatively narrow in ventral view, about 0.6 times as long as gonosubcoxite, with wide base.
